<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="im2int32"><info><pubdate>April, 2006</pubdate></info><refnamediv><refname>im2int32</refname><refpurpose>Convert image to 32-bit signed integers</refpurpose></refnamediv>





<refsynopsisdiv><title>Calling Sequence</title><synopsis>im2 = im2int32(im)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title>
<variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
   <term>im</term>
   <listitem>
     An matrix/image, which can be ANY image supported by SIVP.
   </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
   <term>im2</term>
   <listitem>
     Output image, a 32-bit signed integer matrix.
   </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title>
<para>
<literal>im2int32</literal> convert intensity or RGB images to 32-bit signed integers.
If the input is of class <literal>int32</literal>, the output image is identical to it. 
Otherwise, <literal>im2int32</literal> rescales or offsets the data, and returns the equivalent image of class <literal>int32</literal>.
</para>
</refsection>



